Name: Computer Hardware
Abstract: Relative CPU Performance Data, described in terms of its cycle time, memory size, etc.
RelevantInfo: The estimated relative performance values were estimated by the authors using a linear regression method.  See their article (pp 308-313) for more details on how the relative performance values were set.

AttributeInfo:
1. vendor name: 30 
      (adviser, amdahl,apollo, basf, bti, burroughs, c.r.d, cambex, cdc, dec, 
       dg, formation, four-phase, gould, honeywell, hp, ibm, ipl, magnuson, 
       microdata, nas, ncr, nixdorf, perkin-elmer, prime, siemens, sperry, 
       sratus, wang)
   2. Model Name: many unique symbols
   3. MYCT: machine cycle time in nanoseconds (integer)
   4. MMIN: minimum main memory in kilobytes (integer)
   5. MMAX: maximum main memory in kilobytes (integer)
   6. CACH: cache memory in kilobytes (integer)
   7. CHMIN: minimum channels in units (integer)
   8. CHMAX: maximum channels in units (integer)
   9. PRP: published relative performance (integer)
  10. ERP: estimated relative performance from the original article (integer)
